        "postTitle": "SaRa launches special Eid-ul-Adha collection",
        "postDescription": "Eid is a time to share joy with loved ones — a celebration that invites \nnot just new attire, but a reflection of personal style, taste, and \ncomfort. Embracing this spirit, SaRa Lifestyle introduces its exclusive \nEid-ul-Adha collection, themed 'Roots of Elegance.' This thoughtfully curated collection blends comfort, artistry, and \ncontemporary colours, offering versatile pieces suited for every moment \nof the festivities — whether morning, afternoon, or evening.<br><br><p>This season's designs feature screen prints, sublimation prints, \nembellishments, embroidery, and all-over prints, infused with a festive \nvibe through unique motifs. The collection showcases an array of design \ninspirations including abstract, floral, traditional, and geometric \npatterns. Styles range from Anarkali, princess line, double-layered, \nA-line, symmetric, to asymmetric cuts, with intricate handcrafted \ndetails enhancing each piece. Fabrics used in the collection include \ngeorgette, cotton, viscose, dobby silk, crepe georgette, knit, denim, \nand jacquard cotton.</p>\n<p>For men, SaRa offers an exclusive range including Punjabis, casual \nshirts, formal shirts, t-shirts, polo shirts, denim pants, chino pants, \ncargo pants, vests, and pyjamas.<br><br>SaRa prioritises both quality and affordability, ensuring the collection\n is accessible to a wide range of customers. Prices start from Tk 250 \nand go up to Tk 12,990, catering to diverse tastes and budgets. Among \nthe standout pieces are the exclusive panjabis and sarees that headline \nthis year's Eid collection.<br><br></p><p>Children's offerings include t-shirts, party frocks, cotton frocks, \nthree-piece sets, fashion tops, two-piece sets, and lehengas for girls; \nand single shirts, fashionable shirt-pant sets, panjabis, pyjamas, denim\n pants, knit pants, t-shirts, infant sets, newborn sets, and infant \nPunjabi sets for boys.</p>\n<p>Adding a special touch this Eid, SaRa introduces a family matching \ncollection featuring coordinated outfits for father-son and \nmother-daughter duos, as well as couple-matching ensembles.<br><br></p><p>Founded in May 2018 a sister concern of Snowtex Group, SaRa opened \nits first outlet in Mirpur-6, Dhaka, followed by a second store at \nBashundhara City (Level 1, Block A, Shop 40 and 54). Since then, the \nbrand has expanded to key locations including Mohammadpur (Ring Road, \nBlock F), Uttara (House 22, Sonargaon Janapath, Sector 9), Baridhara (J \nBlock), Banasree (E Block, Road 1), Wari (Rankin Street), Rangpur (Jahaj\n Company Mor), Rajshahi (United Tower, Rani Bazar), Basabo (East Basabo,\n Sabujbagh), Bogura (City Center, Jaleshwari Tola), Sylhet (VIP Road, \nKumarpara), Feni (Ohab Tower), Barishal (Bibir Pukur Par, Fakir Complex,\n Sadar Road), Narayanganj (TNS Plaza, Bangabandhu Road), with plans to \nlaunch a new outlet soon at Shibbari Mor, Khulna.</p>\n<p>Customers can shop directly at these outlets or order online via \nSaRa's official website (saralifestyle.com), Facebook page \n(facebook.com/saralifestyle.bd), or Instagram \n(instagram.com/saralifestyle.bd). For added convenience, the SARA mobile\n app is available for download from the Google Play Store \n(https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.saralifestyle). \nNationwide delivery is available through courier services, bringing \nSARA's Eid collection straight to your doorstep.</p>",
